African infrastructure equity investment manager African Infrastructure Investment Managers (AIIM) has acquired a 60% interest in dry bulk terminal operator DSM Corridor Group Tanzania (DCG), in the Port of Dar es Salaam, in Tanzania. &nbsp;&nbsp; &ldquo;The port and surrounding infrastructure is set to be refurbished under the lauded Dar es Salaam Maritime Gateway project, which is jointly funded by the World Bank, the UK&rsquo;s Department for International Development and TradeMark East Africa,&rdquo; AIIM CEO Jurie Swart said. He added that its strategic location services multiple landlocked countries including Zambia, Uganda, the Democratic Republic of Congo, Rwanda, Burundi and Malawi. &ldquo;Key dry bulk commodities flow through these corridors and the planned rehabilitation of the Central Corridor railway project will further anchor the port as a critical East African hub.&rdquo; &nbsp; Swart noted that the combination of a pressing requirement for greater efficiency at African ports and the development of private investment programmes were driving a strong pipeline of opportunities, particularly in the dry bulk cargo area. &ldquo;This partnership represents an attractive opportunity to support the development of a Pan-African infrastructure platform with a team which has demonstrated immense success in providing a service to both regional and global clients, while ensuring a significant impact on economic and social development in our core markets,&rdquo; he said. &nbsp; &nbsp;